      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "The new snow is lying on the unfavourable surface of an old snowpack. As a consequence of new snow and a sometimes strong wind, large surface-area wind slabs formed in all aspects. The avalanche prone locations are to be found in particular on wind-loaded slopes of all aspects above approximately 1800 m and at transitions from a shallow to a deep snowpack. <br/> Weak layers in the old snowpack are treacherous. In some places the avalanches can be triggered in deep layers of the snowpack and reach large size.",
        "highlights": "In some localities up to 50 cm of snow has fallen. As a consequence of new snow and wind a high avalanche danger will prevail."
