      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "New snow at low altitude. In some localities up to 50 cm of snow has fallen. In some regions up to 30 cm of snow has fallen above approximately 600 m. The new snow is lying on top of a weakly bonded old snowpack. As a consequence of new snow and a sometimes strong northwesterly wind, avalanche prone wind slabs will form in all aspects. Field observations and weak layers in the old snowpack indicate poor snowpack stability."
      },
